Commentary: OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! A confident shout for caught behind but the umpire remains unmoved. Sarfaraz Khan at short leg and Ravichandran Ashwin are convinced but Rishabh Pant isn't sure. Commentary: Sharp turn from the surface! Washington Sundar pitches it on the nagging length on the middle stump line. Rachin Ravindra lunges forward for a defence but the sharp turn beats the outside edge and hits him up on the back thigh. There is a half-hearted appeal from the Indian players around the bat but no one looks interested enough to go for the review. The replays show that the ball pitched in line and the impact was also in line but the ball was clipping the stumps and it would have been umpire's call. The umpires take LUNCH on Day 1 of this Test Match.

Nicely tossed up by Santner from around the wicket, on a fullish length, on middle and leg, Kohli sees the ball above his eyeline and clears his front leg to swipe it across the line. Commentary: OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! Glenn Phillips strikes on his return to the attack. Phillips fires it in from around the wicket, full and attacking the front pad, Sundar presents a straight bat to defend. The ball stays a bit low and catches the inside edge of the bat. It lobs towards short leg where Will Young reacts quickly and sticks out his right hand. The ball lobs off his hand and it results in an easy rebound for him. He takes it by taking a couple of steps to his right. New Zealand started to celebrate but Sundar stood his ground. The third umpire is called into action to check for a bump ball. The replays show that it came off the inside edge onto the pads and lobbed towards short leg. OUT flashes on the big screen.
